 of the layout window (a document)."></property><property name="preserve color numbers" code="RpCn" type="boolean" description="If true, leaves color values unchanged for CMYK objects without embedded profiles and native objects such as line art or type. Note: Converts images whose profiles differ from the profile of the simulated device. Valid only when proofing type is custom."></property><property name="proofing profile" code="WCpp" type="text" description="The profile used for proofing colors."></property><property name="proofing type" code="WCpt" type="PTpt" description="The method of proofing colors."></property><property name="properties" code="qpro" type="record" description="A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time."></property><property name="screen mode" code="smpr" type="scmo" description="The screen mode for layout view."></property><property name="selection" code="sele" description="The selected object(s). Can also accept: object or nothing."><type type="specifier" list="yes"></type></property><property name="selection key object" code="selk" type="page item" description="The key object of the selection. Can also accept: nothing."></property><property name="simulate ink black" code="WCpb" type="boolean" description="If true, simulates the dark gray produced by many printers in place of solid black, according to the proofing profile. Note: Valid only when proofing type is custom."></property><property name="simulate paper white" code="WCpw" type="boolean" description="If true, simulates the dingy white of real paper, according to the proofing profile. Note: Valid only when proofing type is custom."></property><property name="transform reference point" code="rpnt" type="any" description="The default anchor point around which to transform objects. Can return: top left anchor/top center anchor/top right anchor/left center anchor/center anchor/right center anchor/bottom left anchor/bottom center anchor/bottom right anchor or lis