rders in the first alternating column strokes group. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Valid when start column stroke count is 1 or greater. "></property><property name="start column stroke overprint" code="CSof" type="boolean" description="If true, the column borders in the first alternating column strokes group will overprint. Note: Valid when start column stroke count is 1 or greater. "></property><property name="start column stroke tint" code="CStf" type="real" description="The tint (as a percentage) of column borders in the first alternating column strokes group. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Valid when start column stroke count is 1 or greater. "></property><property name="start column stroke type" code="CSsf" type="stroke style" description="The stroke type of columns in the first alternating strokes group. Can also accept: string."></property><property name="start column stroke weight" code="CSwf" description="The stroke weight of column borders in the first alternating column strokes group. Note: Valid when start column stroke count is 1 or greater. "><type type="number"></type><type type="text"></type></property><property name="start row fill color" code="RFcf" type="swatch" description="The fill color, specified as a swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink), of rows in the first alternating fills group. Note: Valid when alternating fills are defined for table rows. "></property><property name="start row fill count" code="RFfc" type="integer" description="The number of rows in the first alternating fills group. Note: Valid when alternating fills are defined for table rows."></property><property name="start row fill overprint" code="RFof" type="boolean" description="If true, the rows in the first alternating fills group will overprint. Note: Valid when alternating fills are defined for table rows. "></property><property name="start row fill tint" code="RFtf" type="real" description="The tint (as a percentage) of the rows in the first alternating fills group. (Range: 0 