r mixed ink) applied to the underline stroke. . Can return: swatch or string."></property><property name="underline gap color" code="ulgc" type="any" description="The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the gap of the underline stroke. Note: Valid when underline type is not solid. Can return: swatch or string."></property><property name="underline gap overprint" code="upgo" type="boolean" description="If true, the gap color of the underline stroke will overprint."></property><property name="underline gap tint" code="ulgt" type="real" description="The tint (as a percentage) of the gap color of the underline stroke. (Range: 0 to 100) Note: Valid when underline type is not solid."></property><property name="underline offset" code="ulos" description="The amount by which to offset the underline from the text baseline."><type type="number"></type><type type="text"></type></property><property name="underline overprint" code="ulop" type="boolean" description="If true, the underline stroke color will overprint."></property><property name="underline tint" code="ultt" type="real" description="The underline stroke tint (as a percentage). (Range: 0 to 100)"></property><property name="underline type" code="ultp" type="any" description="The stroke type of the underline stroke. Can return: stroke style or string."></property><property name="underline weight" code="ulwt" description="The stroke weight of the underline stroke."><type type="number"></type><type type="text"></type></property><property name="vertical scale" code="pvts" type="real" description="The vertical scaling applied to the insertion point."></property><property name="warichu" code="jwar" type="boolean" description="If true, turns on warichu."></property><property name="warichu alignment" code="jwal" type="Jwca" description="The warichu alignment."></property><property name="warichu chars after break" code="jmab" type="integer" description="The minimum number of characters allowed after a line break. "></property><property name="warichu chars before break" code="jmbb" type="integer" description="The minimum number of characters allowed before a line break."></property><property name="warichu line spacing" code="jwls" type="real" description="The gap between lines of warichu characters."></property><property name="warichu lines" code="jwli" type="integer" description="The number of lines of warichu within a single normal line."></property><property name="warichu size" code="jwas" type="real" description="The amount (as a percentage) to scale parent text size to determine warichu size."></property><property name="x offset diacritic" code="diax" type="real" description="The x (horizontal) offset for diacritic adjustment."></property><property name="y offset diacritic" code="diay" type="real" description="The y (vertical) offset for diacritic adjustment."></property></class><class name="kinsoku table" code="Jkst" description="The kinsoku table." plural="kinsoku tables"><element type="event"></element><element type="event listener"></element><property name="cant be separated chars" code="jcbs" type="text" description="The characters in the kinsoku set that cannot be separated."></property><property name="cant begin line chars" code="jcbl" type="text" description="The characters in the kinsoku set that cannot begin lines."></property><property name="cant end line chars" code="jcel" type="text" description="That characters in the kinsoku set that cannot end lines. "></property><property name="class" code="pcls" type="type" access="r" description="The class descriptor type."></property><property name="hanging punctuation chars" code="jhgp" type="text" description="The hanging punctuation characters in the kinsoku set."></property><property name="id" code="ID  " type="integer" access="r" description="The unique ID of the kinsoku table."></property><property name="index" code="pidx" type="integer" access="r" description="The index of the kinsoku table within its containing object."></property><property name="label" code="ptag" type="text" description="A property that can be set to any string."></property><property name="name" code="pnam" type="text" description="The name of the kinsoku table."></property><property name="object reference" code="posp" type="kinsoku table" access="r" description="An object reference for the object."></property><property name="parent" code="pare" type="specifier" access="r" description="The parent of the kinsoku table (a document or application). Can return: document or application."></property><property name="properties" code="qpro" type="record" description="A property that allows setting of several properties at the same time."></property></class><class name="language" code="lang" description="The language on which to base hyphenation rules and spell checking." plural="languages"><element type="event"></element><element type="event listener"></element><property name="class" code="pcls" type="type" access="r" description="The class descriptor type."></property><property name="double quotes" code="ldqu" type="text" description="The double quotes pair for the language."></property><property name="hyphenation vendor" code="lhyv" type="text" description="The hyphenation rules source."></property><property name="icu locale name" code="icul" type="text" access="r" description="The full name of the Language object's ICU locale."></property><property name="id" code="ID  " type="integer" access="r" description="The unique ID of the language."></property><property name="index" code="pidx" type="integer" access="r" description="The index of the language within its containing object."></property><property name="label" code="ptag" type="text" description="A property that can be set to any string."></property><property name="name" code="pnam" type="text" access="r" description="The name of the language."></property><property name="object reference" code="posp" type="language" access="r" description="An object