 0 to 100; to use the inherited or overridden value, use -1.)"></property><property name="stroke weight" code="lnwt" description="The stroke weight applied to the characters of the text."><type type="number"></type><type type="text"></type></property><property name="style overridden" code="stov" type="boolean" access="r" description="If true, the applied style has been overridden with additional attributes."></property><property name="tab list" code="alts" description="A list of the tab stops in the paragraph. Can return: list of record."><type type="any" list="yes"></type></property><property name="tatechuyoko" code="jtcy" type="boolean" description="If true, makes the character horizontal in vertical text."></property><property name="tatechuyoko X offset" code="jtax" type="real" description="The horizontal offset for horizontal characters in vertical text."></property><property name="tatechuyoko Y offset" code="jtay" type="real" description="The vertical offset for horizontal characters in vertical text."></property><property name="tracking" code="trak" type="real" description="The amount by which to loosen or tighten a block of text, specified in thousands of an em."></property><property name="trailing aki" code="jmas" type="real" description="The amount of space after each character."></property><property name="treat ideographic space as space" code="jisb" type="boolean" description="If true, ideographic spaces will not wrap to the next line like text characters."></property><property name="tsume" code="tsum" type="real" description="The amount of horizontal character compression."></property><property name="underline" code="undr" type="boolean" description="If true, underlines the text."></property><property name="underline color" code="ulco" type="any" description="The swatch (color, gradient, tint, or mixed ink) applied to the underline stroke. . Can return: swatch or string."></property><property name="underline gap color" code="ulgc" type="any" description=