ncy and anti-aliasing."></enumerator><enumerator name="default" code="Dflt" description="Uses the container object's default display performance preferences setting. For information, see default display settings."></enumerator></enumeration><enumeration name="ahed" code="ahed"><enumerator name="none" code="none" description="None."></enumerator><enumerator name="simple arrow head" code="simp" description="An arrow head formed by two slanting lines whose intersection forms a 45-degree angle and whose stroke weight is the same as the path's stroke."></enumerator><enumerator name="simple wide arrow head" code="swah" description="An arrow head formed by two slanting lines whose intersection forms a 90-degree angle and whose stroke weight is the same as the path's stroke."></enumerator><enumerator name="triangle arrow head" code="trin" description="A solid triangle arrow head whose point describes a 45-degree angle."></enumerator><enumerator name="triangle wide arrow head" code="twah" description="A solid triangle arrow head whose point describes a 90-degree angle."></enumerator><enumerator name="barbed arrow head" code="barb" description="A solid arrow head whose pierced end bows sharply toward the point and whose point describes a 45-degree angle."></enumerator><enumerator name="curved arrow head" code="cvah" description="A solid arrow head whose pierced end concaves toward the point and whose point describes a 45-degree angle."></enumerator><enumerator name="circle arrow head" code="crah" description="A hollow circle whose outline is the same weight as the stroke. The circle's diameter is 5 times the stroke width."></enumerator><enumerator name="circle solid arrow head" code="csah" description="A solid circle whose diameter is 5 times the stroke width."></enumerator><enumerator name="square arrow head" code="sqah" description="A hollow square set perpendicular to the path, whose outline is the same weight as the stroke. The length of one side of the square is 5 times 